This paper deals with sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses machine learning techniques such as logistic regression and recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves data extraction and analysis, which can be categorized under information retrieval (cs.IR) and social media analysis (cs.SI).
